OL,3,CDrilling Antarctica: What ice can tell
OL,4,Cus about our past and the future
OL,6,FTo get it out, scientists had to bore
OL,7,Fdown carefully, pulling the ice out
OL,8,Fbit by bit on spring loaders as the
OL,9,Fhole is filled with a liquid so it
OL,10,Fdoes not refreeze.
OL,12,FThe ice core has been split into parts
OL,13,Fand sent to labs across Europe
OL,14,Fincluding the British Antarctic Survey
OL,15,Fin Cambridge.
OL,17,FScientists will melt the ice and
OL,18,Fanalyse its contents, with the results
OL,19,Fexpected to give us new information
OL,20,Fabout Earth's history.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
