OL,3,CDrilling Antarctica: What ice can tell
OL,4,Cus about our past and the future
OL,6,FThat's because tiny bubbles of air
OL,7,Flocked inside the ice have been frozen
OL,8,Fin time.
OL,10,FThe bubbles in the younger ice are
OL,11,Fbigger, but in the older ice, the
OL,12,Fbubbles have been squeezed down for
OL,13,Fsuch a long time that it looks like
OL,14,Fglass.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
