OL,3,CDrilling Antarctica: What ice can tell
OL,4,Cus about our past and the future
OL,6,FIce Core Drilling Engineer, James
OL,7,FVeale explained: "When you get this
OL,8,Fdeep, the pressure from the ice is so
OL,9,Fgreat, those air bubbles get smaller
OL,10,Fand smaller and compressed until you
OL,11,Fget to the very bottom and you can't
OL,12,Fsee them at all."
OL,14,FSome of these bubbles have been
OL,15,Ftrapped in stasis for over a million
OL,16,Fyears.
OL,18,FThey are so old that these tiny bits
OL,19,Fof perfectly preserved air would have
OL,20,Fbeen breathed in by giant mammoths
OL,21,Fwhen they roamed the Earth.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
