OL,3,CDrilling Antarctica: What ice can tell
OL,4,Cus about our past and the future
OL,6,FIn fact it is so accurate, scientists
OL,7,Fcan see the start of the industrial
OL,8,Frevolution and even the moment that
OL,9,Flead was taken out of petrol.
OL,11,FThe last long ice core to be drilled
OL,12,Fout went back 800,000 years. It helped
OL,13,Fmap out how the earth's temperature
OL,14,Fand carbon cycles have fluctuated.
OL,16,FHead of ice core research at British
OL,17,FAntarctic Survey, Dr Liz Thomas, and
OL,18,Fher team will be slowly melting the
OL,19,Fice for 15 hours a day for the next
OL,20,Fseven weeks so they can analyse the
OL,21,Fgases in the ice.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
