OL,3,CDrilling Antarctica: What ice can tell
OL,4,Cus about our past and the future
OL,6,FThe Earth does fluctuate between ice
OL,7,Fages and higher temperature eras, but
OL,8,Fthe ice core has revealed that there
OL,9,Fhas never been this much CO2 put into
OL,10,Fthe atmosphere this quickly in the
OL,11,Fentire 800,000 year record.
OL,13,FWith the new core, scientists will be
OL,14,Fable to nearly double the length of
OL,15,Fcurrent records. It is hoped it will
OL,16,Freveal new data to explain why the
OL,17,FEarth's temperature cycle changed from
OL,18,Fice ages every 40,000 years to every
OL,19,F100,000 years.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
